35.36	Estrogen_receptor	Estrogen receptor	Estrogen receptor refers to a group of receptors that are activated by the hormone 17Î²-estradiol (estrogen). Two types of estrogen receptor exist: ER, which is a member of the nuclear hormone family of intracellular receptors, and the estrogen G protein-coupled receptor GPR30 (GPER), which is a G protein-coupled receptor. This article refers to the nuclear hormone receptor ER.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8b/PBB_Protein_ESR1_image.png/220px-PBB_Protein_ESR1_image.png
